BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (One day, Kalu asked his grandmother, the oldest and wisest elephant in the herd, 'Grandma,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td (why am I so scared?') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (Grandmother Elephant wrapped her trunk around him gently. 'Everyone is afraid of) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td (something, little one.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td ('Even you?' Kalu asked, his eyes wide.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td ('Even me,' she said. 'I'm afraid of losing the ones I love. But fear doesn't make you) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td (weak, Kalu. What you DO with your fear   that's what matters.') Tj ET
