BT /F2 11 Tf 54 716.0 Td (Page 19) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (The next day, when the flood waters had calmed and it was time to cross the river again,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Kalu walked to the front of the line.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (His legs were still wobbly. His heart was still thumping. The water still scared him.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td (But this time, he didn't stand frozen on the bank. He took a deep breath, thought of) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td (little Kofi, and stepped in.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td (One step. Then another. Then another. Scared the whole time. But moving forward anyway.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 596.4 Td ([Illustration: Kalu at the front of the elephant line, bravely stepping into the now-calm) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 582.4 Td (river, still visibly nervous but determined, with the whole herd watching proudly behind) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 568.4 Td (him]) Tj ET
endstream
